summary: I talked about Kate in the last ask I received, and I found some prime™ art sdoihdssd I decided to redraw the main cast. Her...
caption:
I talked about Kate in the last ask I received, and I found some prime™ art sdoihdssd

I decided to redraw the main cast. Her story was the first one I really got invested I guess, I wrote a lot for it (Its all garbage and I can’t go through it because it makes me cringe so much sdbiodsndsk)

Please forgive the quality of the phone pictures ;;; Those drawings date from when I was in elementary school! Probably around 5th or 6th grade but I’m really not sure! Honestly, the original (that I can’t find;;) could date from evenn 4th grade sdusdjkn And the last one dates from 2015-ish (maybe 2016)

Kevin was the main love interest but tbh he was kind of a dick (they all were tho…..) Miyako was in love with Kevin and Naru is her big brother, I don’t remember anything else about her. Naru was a second love interest, he was a police investigator, that was working on the case of Kate, and he fell in love with her (I think?) but uuuhhh that’s shady af ¯\_(ツ)_/¯

Also the last bits I wrote, I think Kate had like a big sister and she was a legendary thief or something……… Weird shit was happening™

blog.name: autonomy1
blog.title: Peter Percival-AUTONOMY
blog.description: Shades, nuances, scraps of existence......looking directly at an object can sometimes be a meaningless, even a destructive use of time…in society we are trained to look at things quickly, process that information and move on to another view…so much information and meaning can be lost in the action of moving on….by changing the expected angle of view, or re-arranging elements of an image one can derive another meaning from it, and if not an absolute meaning an abstract one which makes us look once again…that is all one can ask for, another look…(©) Pete Percival - 2013 All Rights Reserved. Reproduction of any kind is illegal.
